<p>I have a string which I am cutting down to 200 chars, and then adding <code>...</code> with the following:</p>  <pre><code>$role = get_field('the_role'); $role = substr($role, 0, 200); $role = $role.'...'; </code></pre>  <p>The problem is, this string can sometimes contain basic HTML like <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;b&gt;</code></p>  <p>If the 200 chars lands halfway through a tag, the HTML is broken. For example:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;circa £55k pro rata – full-time, 10 month contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;To develop and communicate credible and evidence-based policies using key data from service delivery activities.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p...&lt; div=""&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How can I adjust my PHP code above to count to 200 characters, but ensure any HTML tags are closed?</p>  <p>This block of text is a good example of what I am dealing with:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;circa £55k pro rata – full-time, 10 month contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;To develop and communicate credible and evidence-based policies using key data from service delivery activities.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p|&gt;To develop and implement campaigns and influencing activities.&lt;/p&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>I have placed a | symbol at the 200 char mark. I would need to cut at the end of the previous <code>&lt;/p&gt;</code></strong></p>